As a Teaching Fellow for the required foundations module at the Harvard Graduate School of Education for master's students, I aided in covering materials encompassing major forms of evidence including descriptive quantitative/qualitative, causal experimental/quasi-experimental, synthetic, and process. I was responsible for facilitating student discussion of assigned readings, supervision of project development, grading daily forum discussion posts/quizzes, and evaluation of final group project presentations. In my role as a Teaching Fellow, via team-based learning approaches, I bolstered student learning of understanding what makes for stronger/weaker evidence of various types and using evidence to inform decisions rooted in authentic problems of practice.
